keywords = {Blockchain technology, Healthcare, Decentralization, Security, Reliability, Transparency, Immutability},
abstract = {With the revolution in network technology and the Internet of things (IoT), pervasive computing becomes tangible by its usage in abundant applications at the global level, including the healthcare industry. It enables billions of objects to communicate purposefully with high-speed data processing (data transfer, collection, management, and processing) particularly in the 5G-enabled healthcare industry/environment. The evolution in the healthcare industry has grown exponentially from Healthcare 1.0 to 4.0. The evolution originated with Healthcare 1.0, which was doctor centric, and was subsequently followed by Healthcare 2.0 where manual records were made digital, and Healthcare 3.0 in which the technology became patient centric. Next, Healthcare 4.0 was equipped with advanced digital technologies such as IoT, cloud computing, and fog computing for sharing or communicating the data between various stakeholders such as doctors, patients, laboratories, nurses, relatives/caretakers, etc. As communication became easy and in real time in Healthcare 4.0, it utilizes a centralized architecture suffering from major issues such as access control mechanisms, security, and privacy. Majorally, the challenges include a longer time in retrieval and storage of data from heterogeneous devices as well as threats of tampering of sensitive medical records of patients/hospitals. The issue related to the access control mechanism can be resolved by 5G healthcare, which introduces a high data speed, low latency, increased reliability, availability, and massive network capacity in the current healthcare framework. In addition, the concerns of privacy and security can be resolved by adopting Blockchain technology in 5G healthcare. This emerging technology supports both the privacy and security of sensitive data by offering a safe and trustworthy secure system to record and share these data. The data, once encrypted using this technology, cannot be modified later. Thus, Blockchain 